JOE Aribo has reaffirmed his stance on a potential exit from Rangers, saying his focus is solely on his football. The Nigerian star has been the subject of transfer interest from the English Premier League, after a mammoth season at Ibrox. Aribo has been heavily linked with a move to Crystal Palace, with Steven Gerrard also said to be keen on a swoop for his Aston Villa side.   BetKing empowers 100 entrepreneurs     Besiktas renews interest in Ighalo     AURÉLIEN TCHOUAMÉNI: I want to leave my mark on history   The Super Eagles man is keen to wave off any distraction of transfer talk, despite being in the last year of his current Ibrox deal. He told BBC Sport Africa: “With all that stuff I don’t really read into it and I just focus on my football because you can’t have distractions as it won’t allow you to play the best and be the best that you want to be. “Which is obviously what I want to be every time I play. I just want to be focused and ready to go.” He added: “Playing in different positions has helped me realise what I’m capable of doing and also given me an opportunity to keep growing.